## Product Options — Quality Standards

When the agent produces an options result, it must feel like a real recommendation
from someone who actually researched it. Not a list of Amazon links.

### What a Real Options Result Looks Like

```json
{
  "options": [
    {
      "name": "Herb Garden Starter Kit by Back to the Roots",
      "price": "$54.99",
      "store": "Amazon",
      "url": "https://amazon.com/dp/B07...",
      "image_url": "https://...",
      "why": "Top rated, self-watering, great for beginners — fits your $60 budget",
      "rating": "4.6 ★ (2,847 reviews)",
      "delivery": "Free delivery, arrives in 2 days"
    }
  ]
}
```

Every field must be real. No made-up prices. No made-up URLs. No generic descriptions.

### How the Options Agent Gets There

The agent must do real work to find these:

```
Step 1 → search("herb garden kit gift under $60")
  → get product names, stores, approximate prices

Step 2 → fetch(product_page_url)
  → get exact price, real product name, real image, real rating, real delivery

Step 3 → repeat for 3 candidates

Step 4 → rank by fit (budget, context, rating)

Step 5 → return exactly 3 — best fit first
```

The fetch step is mandatory for options. Search results have stale prices.
Fetch the actual product page to get current accurate data.

### Options Agent Rules

- Exact product name — not a category. "Herb Garden Kit" is wrong.
  "Herb Garden Starter Kit by Back to the Roots" is right.
- Real price from the actual page — not estimated.
- Real purchase URL — not a search results page.
- Store name shown — Amazon, Target, Etsy, etc.
- `why` field is specific to the user's context — not generic.
  "Great for beginners" is wrong. "Fits your $60 budget and she gardens outdoors" is right.
- Max 3 options. Always exactly 3 if possible.
- If fewer than 3 real options found → return what you have, note it.
- Never return Amazon search URLs. Only direct product URLs.

### SerpApi for Product Search (optional upgrade)

For more structured product data, use SerpApi Google Shopping:

```
GET https://serpapi.com/search
  engine=google_shopping
  q=herb garden kit gift
  gl=us
```

Returns: title, price, purchase_link, rating, store — structured.
More reliable than scraping. $50/month.

For MVP: Tavily + fetch is enough. Upgrade to SerpApi when product
data quality becomes a user complaint.

