## Code Quality Standards

Every file in Pem follows these standards. Non-negotiable.

### Structure

```typescript
/**
 * PrepWorker — BullMQ processor for individual prep jobs.
 *
 * Picks up prep jobs from the queue, runs the agentic loop,
 * and saves the result. Each job is one thought from a dump.
 *
 * Flow: enrich context → run agent → quality check → save → notify
 */
@Processor('preps')
export class PrepWorker {
  constructor(
    private readonly agentService: AgentService,
    private readonly prepsRepo: PrepsRepository,
    private readonly pushService: PushService,
    private readonly stepsService: StepsService,
  ) {}

  /**
   * Process a single prep job.
   * Called by BullMQ when a job is dequeued.
   */
  @Process('run-prep')
  async handle(job: Job<PrepJob>): Promise<void> {
    ...
  }
}
```

### Rules for All Code

- Every class has a JSDoc comment explaining what it does and why
- Every public method has a JSDoc comment
- Every file has a single clear responsibility
- No inline magic strings — use constants or enums
- No any types — strict TypeScript everywhere
- Errors are typed — never `catch (e: any)`
- All async operations are awaited — no floating promises
- Repository pattern — DB queries never in controllers or services directly
- Services never import other services directly — use dependency injection
- Environment variables accessed through a typed config service, never `process.env` directly

### Naming Conventions

```
Controllers  → PrepsController
Services     → PrepsService
Repositories → PrepsRepository
Workers      → PrepWorker
Agents       → SearchAgent, DraftAgent, ClassifyAgent
Tools        → SearchTool, FetchTool (as tool() instances)
DTOs         → CreateDumpDto, ArchivePrepDto
Schemas      → PrepResultSchema, ThoughtSchema (Zod)
Types        → PrepStatus, PrepRenderType (TypeScript enums)
```

### Error Handling Pattern

```typescript
// Every agent and worker catches specifically, never broadly
try {
  const result = await this.agentService.run(thought, context)
  await this.prepsRepo.markReady(prepId, result)
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof TavilyRateLimitError) {
    // retry after delay — let BullMQ handle it
    throw error
  }
  if (error instanceof AgentOutputError) {
    // bad output — mark failed, don't retry
    await this.prepsRepo.markFailed(prepId, error.message)
    return
  }
  // unknown — log and rethrow for BullMQ retry
  this.logger.error('PrepWorker.handle failed', { prepId, error })
  throw error
}
```

### Logging Pattern

Use NestJS Logger. Structured, consistent.

```typescript
private readonly logger = new Logger(PrepWorker.name)

this.logger.log('Starting prep', { prepId, thought, stepCount: 0 })
this.logger.log('Step complete', { prepId, tool: step.toolName, stepNumber })
this.logger.log('Prep ready', { prepId, renderType, durationMs })
this.logger.error('Prep failed', { prepId, error: error.message })
```

