## SSE — Backend Architecture Detail

The BullMQ worker and the SSE endpoint need to communicate.
They run in separate contexts (worker process vs HTTP process).

Use Redis pub/sub as the bridge:

```
BullMQ worker finishes prep
    ↓
Publish to Redis channel: `prep-events:${dumpId}`
    ↓
SSE service subscribes to that channel
    ↓
Pushes event to connected client
```

```typescript
// in worker — after prep is ready
await this.redis.publish(
  `prep-events:${dumpId}`,
  JSON.stringify({ type: 'prep.ready', prep: readyPrep })
)

// in SSE service
const subject = new Subject<MessageEvent>()
this.redis.subscribe(`prep-events:${dumpId}`, (message) => {
  subject.next({ data: message })
})
return subject.asObservable()
```

This works even if worker and HTTP server are separate Railway services.

